com.edugility.liquibase

Class URLResourceAccessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • liquibase.resource.AbstractResourceAccessor
      • com.edugility.liquibase.URLResourceAccessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ResourceAccessor

    public class URLResourceAccessor
extends AbstractResourceAccessor
    An AbstractResourceAccessor that delegates most of its work to a delegate ResourceAccessor, while preserving the ability to process Strings that represent URLs.

    Design Notes

    The Liquibase 3.3.0 ResourceAccessor interface is inconsistently documented, and mixes several quite unrelated concerns together. The CompositeResourceAccessor implicitly relies on non-null values being returned from some of its aggregated ResourceAccessors' methods. The combination of these two unfortunate facts means that returning null from methods that do not make sense for a ResourceAccessor like this one that processes URLs is effectively impossible. Consequently, a delegating approach has to be taken instead.

    Author:
    Laird Nelson

    AbstractResourceAccessor, CompositeResourceAccessor, ResourceAccessor

    • Method Detail

      • getResourcesAsStream

        public Set<InputStream> getResourcesAsStream(String path)
                                      throws IOException
        Returns a Set of open InputStreams that the supplied path logically designates, or null if there is no resource that can be identified with the supplied path, per the contract of the ResourceAccessor.getResourcesAsStream(String) method.

        This method may return null if there is no resource that can be identified by the supplied path.

        This implementation attempts to create a URL from the supplied path, and, if that operation is successful, to return a Set containing only that URL. If a MalformedURLException is encountered during this operation, then null is returned instead.

        Parameters:
        path - a String that will be passed unaltered to the constructor of the URL class; must not be null
        Returns:
        a Set of open InputStreams, or null
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if path is null
        IOException - if an input/output error occurs
        See Also:
        ResourceAccessor.getResourcesAsStream(String)
